# UDS Figma Component Card

Specification for the canvas layout used on every component page in the `UDS Components` Figma file. One frame per component, named `udc-<id>-page`, holding seven cards in a fixed order. The component sets, sub-components, and instance previews live INSIDE these cards ŌĆö they are never loose top-level nodes.

## Why this rule exists

Component pages used to be a pile of unlabeled component sets sprawled at random positions. This rule defines the canonical "card" treatment so:
- Every page reads the same way (same card order, same eyebrows, same status colors)
- Future agents and skills produce identical output without re-deciding layout questions
- A designer-authored template documents the canonical layout in Figma so the recipe in the builder script always has a visual reference to be measured against
- Token bindings are forced ŌĆö no raw hex anywhere

## Direction of data flow (CRITICAL)

This rule covers **code ŌåÆ Figma** writes, opposite of most UDS sync work. The card builder READS from `uds-docs/uds/components/<id>/spec.json` and WRITES card structure into the UDS Components Figma file. It must follow:

- [`uds-figma-write-safety.mdc`](./uds-figma-write-safety.mdc) ŌĆö Figma writes are denied by default; this skill writes only when the user explicitly invokes it. Every write must produce the standard "Figma write summary" report.
- [`uds-source-of-truth.mdc`](./uds-source-of-truth.mdc) ŌĆö `uds-docs/uds/` is read-only for this skill. Never modifies spec/status/changelog/impl/css under that path. Reads only.
- [`uds-figma-preflight.mdc`](./uds-figma-preflight.mdc) ŌĆö discovery and read-only inspection always come before any write.

If an audit finding suggests the spec or component CSS should change, surface it as a recommendation; do not edit `uds-docs/uds/`. The authorized write paths into `uds-docs/uds/` are the named Figma-sync skills (`import-figma-tokens`, `sync-figma-component-spec`, `sync-figma-component-status`, `link-figma-nodes`, `new-component`) ŌĆö not this one.

## File target

- **`UDS Components`** (file key `1XJoUJgtNpw4R0IIT3VjoK`) ŌĆö the only Figma file this skill writes to. Per [`uds-figma-write-safety.mdc`](./uds-figma-write-safety.mdc), every write requires explicit user direction naming the component(s) to build.

Token bindings come from the `UDS Tokens` library (file key `iqKgR73ubUHpQTIcF7XGMy`); subscribe it to the file before binding anything.

## Page wrapper anatomy

```
udc-<id>-page (FRAME, 2800w, hug height, fill: page-subtle, radius: container-xl, clipsContent: true)
Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ status-accent (RECTANGLE, 2800├Ś8, status-tinted gradient ŌĆö wrapper-level, clipped by wrapper corners)
Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ content (FRAME, FILL w, hug h, autolayout V, gap: space/1000, padding: space/800)
Ōöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ HEADER          (light card, taller padding)
Ōöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ ANATOMY         (light card)  ŌåÉ optional, omit for placeholder pages
Ōöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ VARIANTS        (light card)  ŌåÉ omit if no inspectable component sets
Ōöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ SUB-COMPONENTS  (light card)  ŌåÉ omit if no underscored components
Ōöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ USAGE           (light card)
Ōöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ ACCESSIBILITY   (light card)  ŌåÉ optional, requires accessibility.keyboard
Ōöé   ŌööŌöĆŌöĆ META            (light card, taller padding)
```

The page wrapper itself is rounded (`uds/border/radius/container-xl`,
matching the inner cards) and clips its content, so the
`status-accent` strip at the top inherits the wrapper's rounded
top-left and top-right corners. The wrapper has no stroke ŌĆö the
rounded silhouette against the Figma canvas background reads as
"a single page document floating on the canvas."

The page is positioned at `(0, 0)`. Component sets are reparented INTO the appropriate cards ŌĆö never duplicated, never left at top level.

## Card recipe (universal)

After the 2026-05-12 design revision, **every card on every component
page uses the same light-surface recipe.** The earlier "dark card"
treatment for HEADER and META was retired because translucent-white text
on `surface-xxbold` failed WCAG AA contrast in several theme modes (see
the accessibility note below for context).

| Property | Token / value |
|---|---|
| Fill | `uds/color/surface/surface-main` |
| Stroke | 1px `uds/color/border/border-tertiary` |
| Radius | `uds/border/radius/container-xl` (24px) |
| Effects | Dual drop shadow: `0,1,3,0 @ 4%` + `0,12,32,-4 @ 5%` |
| Inner padding (most cards) | `uds/space/800` (64px) |
| Inner padding (HEADER + META) | `uds/space/1000` (80px) ŌĆö taller because they carry the bookending content |
| Inner item gap (most cards) | `uds/space/400` (32px) |
| Inner item gap (HEADER inner row) | `uds/space/600` (48px) between left column and hero preview |
| Inner item gap (META inner) | `uds/space/500` (40px) between sec-head / links-row / divider / meta-row |
| ClipsContent | true |

HEADER additionally has an 8px-tall top accent strip in
`uds/color/border/<status>` (gradient: 0.3 ŌåÆ 1 ŌåÆ 0.3 alpha) directly
above the inner row, just inside the rounded-corner clip. The 2800├Ś8
wrapper-level `status-accent` strip at the top of `udc-<id>-page` and
the 2672├Ś4 HEADER inner strip are both intentional ŌĆö the outer strip is
the page-level status marker, the inner strip is the card-level marker.

### Why light cards everywhere

The first iteration paired `surface-xxbold` (near-black) HEADER/META
cards with `text-inverse` (near-white) text. That works in light mode
but inverts incorrectly under several theme modes (ResMan Dark,
Inhabit Light's amber surface variants) and produces text below 4.5:1
contrast against the actual rendered surface color. Settling on
`surface-main` + `text-primary` for every card moves the design within
the AA-safe surface tokens documented in
`uds-token-architecture.mdc#accessibility-contract`.

## Numbered eyebrow (every section)

Identical pattern across all 7 sections. The number is the only thing that changes (`01` HEADER, `02` ANATOMY, `03` VARIANTS, `04` SUB-COMPONENTS, `05` USAGE, `06` ACCESSIBILITY, `07` META).

```
[mono number 48-56pt]  Ōöé 1px├Ś32-40 vertical bar  Ōöé KICKER (mono 11-12pt, +8% tracking)
                                                  ┬Ę / section-name (mono 11pt, muted)
```

| Field | Value |
|---|---|
| Number font | Geist Mono Medium, `48px / 48` (cards) or `56px / 56` (HEADER) |
| Number color | `uds/color/text/<status>` (e.g. `text-warning` for in-progress) |
| Vertical bar | 1├Ś32-40 rectangle, fill `uds/color/border/<status>` at 0.4-0.5 opacity |
| Kicker | Geist Mono Medium 11-12, +8% tracking, `text-<status>` |
| Sub-label | Geist Mono Regular 11, `text-secondary` (every section, since all cards are light) |

Kicker text per section:

| Section | Kicker | Sub-label |
|---|---|---|
| HEADER | `COMPONENT` | (none ŌĆö see note) |
| ANATOMY | `STATES & VISUAL` | `┬Ę / anatomy` |
| VARIANTS | `COMPONENT VARIANTS` | `┬Ę / variants` |
| SUB-COMPONENTS | `COMPOSITION` | `┬Ę / sub-components` |
| USAGE | `GUIDELINES` | `┬Ę / usage` |
| ACCESSIBILITY | `A11Y / WCAG` | `┬Ę / accessibility` |
| META | `RESOURCES & OWNERS` | `┬Ę / meta` |

HEADER intentionally has no sub-label as of 2026-05-12. Earlier versions
showed `uds-components / <UDS_VERSION>` here, but that displayed the same
information on every component card and required every card to be
rebuilt on every UDS release without adding any decision-supporting
information ŌĆö the canonical UDS version lives in
`uds-docs/uds/version.json#version` and on the `UDS Version: X.Y` Figma
page. The eyebrow's `eb-col` wrapper for HEADER now contains just the
kicker text node; keep the wrapper for structural symmetry with other
sections, even though it's a single-child column.

The META status pill is also intentionally version-free for the same
reason: the pill label is the bare status string from the Status ŌåÆ token
map table (`IN PROGRESS`, `BLOCKED`, etc.), with no `┬Ę UDS X.Y` suffix.

