## Pill row (HEADER, just under description)

Horizontal auto-layout, items in this exact order:

1. **Status pill** ŌĆö `surface-<status>` at 0.18 opacity bg, 1px `border-<status>` stroke, full-radius. Contents: 8px ellipse `icon-<status>`, Geist Mono Medium 12 label (uppercase, +8% tracking, `text-<status>`).
2. **CSS chip** ŌĆö `surface-subtle` bg, 1px `border-tertiary` stroke, full-radius. Contents: Geist Mono Regular 12 `text-secondary`, value `uds/components/<id>/<id>.css` (the on-disk path).
3. **Spacer** (auto-fill, takes remaining space).

Earlier versions of this rule defined two trailing items ŌĆö a "View docs"
button and a "Storybook" button ŌĆö in this row. Both were removed on
2026-05-12 because the links didn't work and there was already a richer
treatment for the same destinations in the META section's link cards.
Don't add new trailing items here without a design conversation.

